http://www.finseth.com/craft/

A book about editor design from 1991, with an appendix listing EmacsImplementations.
The author, Craig Finseth studied at MIT and was heavily influenced by Emacs culture and editor design.
Publishing rights reverted to the author so it is published online. The book was updated in 2000 or so.
It uses GNU Emacs for many of its examples.

The book has recently been published in Paperback format by Lulu and can be found [http://www.lulu.com/content/paperback-book/the-craft-of-text-editing/237969 here]. There is also an Amazon [http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1411682971 page] for the book. The book has been issued the ISBN 9781411682979. It is also freely available on this [http://www.finseth.com/craft/ page] in PDF format.

See also CraigFinseth.

